<body>
<div is-="typography-block">
    <h1>ANDREW WALPOLE</h1>
    <h2>TECH LEAD | FULL-STACK ENGINEER | AWS CERTIFIED EXPERT</h2>

    <section is-="typography-block">
        <h1>Get future-ready</h1>
        <p>As a technology leader and engineer, I view programming as a product-centric activity. My expertise
            encompasses both back-end and front-end development, emphasising serverless, event-driven architecture and
            systems thinking. On the front-end, I strive for solutions that combine accessibility, usability, and
            performance. I enthusiastically endorse The Agile Manifesto and the systems thinking and domain-driven
            approach now prevalent in our industry. Over my career, I’ve played instrumental roles in significant retail
            tech initiatives including projects for Tesco, Boots, and Sainsbury's.</p>

        <p>Most recently, I guided tech teams for NBrown’s SimplyBe and Castle projects.</p>

        <ul marker-="pen tree open">
            <li>Positioned the fintech project, Castle, to launch with its first customers in January 2026.</li>
            <li>Delivered full platform relaunch of Simply Be in the autumn of 2022; guided three cross-functional
                squads in creating a React.js/Next.js monorepo from several different repos, resulting in a successful
                go-live and improvements in platform performance and stability.
            </li>
            <li>The successful work on the “new web” and the Castle project directly lead to a £181m takeover of NBrown
                in December 2024.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <p>I was also pivotal in creating Elevaate, which secured £600k in funding and won Startup of the Year at Retail
            Week Live 2015.</p>

        <p>My experience spans all levels, from infrastructure to the browser</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h1>Services Offered</h1>

        <section class="grid">
            <article class="grid-item">
                <h2>Full-Stack Development</h2>
                <span class="icon">
                <Image
                        src={Development}
                        widths={[50, 100, Development.width]}
                        sizes={`(max-width: 800px) 50px, (max-width: max) 100px`}
                        alt="A description of my image."
                />
                </span>
                <pre>andywalpole@Andys-IMac-5 portfolio % echo "I craft comprehensive web solutions with a focus on user-centric design." >> development.txt</pre>
            </article>
            <article class="grid-item">
                <h2>Technical Leadership</h2>
                <span class="icon">
                <Image
                        src={LeadershipIcon}
